title: Replay Phantom’s SuperCoach blog here | The
text:
FACING a huge break-even of 196 in Round 15, Gary Ablett did his best to get close, tallying 30 possessions, one goal and 153 SuperCoach points against the Bulldogs.
Even so, a further $19k dropped off Ablett’s price tag leaving him worth $669k.
With a break-even of 119 heading into Round 16 — a score he has reached in 16 of his past 19 games ­— it’s now time to move on the little master.
Scroll to the bottome to see The Phantom’s team from last week
After Nat Fyfe’s back-to-back scores below 90, Ablett, the SuperCoach king, is ready to reclaim his throne.
How are you planning to bring Ablett in?
Join The Phantom here from 12.30pm CST to talk trade plans and all things SuperCoach.
